options: Returns the value of attribute options
recall: Returns the value of attribute recall
set: Returns the value of attribute set
named_route: Returns the value of attribute named_route
normalize_recall!: Set 'index' as default action for recall
normalize_controller_action_id!:
This pulls :controller, :action, and :id out of the recall.
The recall key is only used if there is no key in the options
or if the key in the options is identical. If any of
:controller, :action or :id is not found, don't pull any
more keys from the recall.
use_relative_controller!:
if the current controller is "foo/bar/baz" and controller: "baz/bat"
is specified, the controller becomes "foo/baz/bat"
normalize_action!: Move 'index' action from options to recall
generate:
Generates a path from routes, returns [path, params].
If no route is generated the formatter will raise ActionController::UrlGenerationError
